ribed with CYP450 3A4 inhibitors, particularly potent and moderate inhibitors (e.', 'Major', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/288747/', '[1] Hutchinson MR, Menelaou A, Foster DJ, Coller JK, Somogyi AA "CYP2D6 and CYP3A4 involvement in the primary oxidative metabolism of hydrocodone by human liver microsomes." Br J Clin Pharmacol 57 (2004):  287-97[2] "Product Information. Zohydro ER (hydrocodone)." Zogenix, Inc  (2013):', 'Tinidazole, Pantoprazole, Levofloxacin, Dexlansoprazole, Rabeprazole, Sucralfate, Tetracycline, Misoprostol, Bismuth subcitrate potassium, Metronidazole, Famotidine, More', NULL, 1767369485);
